    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Thin rounds of cooked dough typically made from nixtamalized cornmeal pressed into shape by hand or with a press. Traditionaly cooked on a 'comal', it is a staple of the Mesoamerican diet. The term in Nahuatl means "cooked thing".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
